Name: X-linked dominant hypophosphatemic rickets
Definition: A rickets has_material_basis in X-linked mutations in the PHEX gene that lead to increased circulating levels of FGF-23

Name: hereditary hypophosphatemic rickets with hypercalciuria
Definition: A rickets that has_material_basis_in increased serum 1

Name: autosomal dominant hypophosphatemic rickets
Definition: A rickets characterized by low levels of serum phosphate and elevated levels of ALP and phosphaturia and that has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

Name: autosomal recessive hypophosphatemic rickets
Definition: A rickets that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance mutation in the DMP1 gene and is characterized by hypophosphatemia

Name: X-linked recessive hypophosphatemic rickets
Definition: A rickets that has_material_basis_in mutation in the CLCN5 gene on chromosome Xp11.22.
